9:
Put a lid on it! You always start
screaming out of nowhere.
13:
I think I have a right to! There was a
reason the coup d'Ã©tat was planned
when he wasn't around!
20:
But for now I am the humble guest
of Sir Nimbus. I have no intention of
overthrowing the current
government. You may even take my
blade, as a show of good will.
24:
F-forgive the impertinence, but we
couldn't possibly hold ourselves
responsible for such a sword. We will
trust you.
31:
Hold up! I was expecting a maniacal
hound, but he seems like a good
guy!
36:
Good might be overselling him, but
yeah, he's at least a knight, tried and
true.
40:
Yep! Our side couldn't beat him
once... across a whole decade! What
if he's got something sinister
planned?
45:
Ha. I have been routed. Though I've
dealt with a hundred foes, I've yet
learned to wrangle a few children.
47: Yay! I beat the big knight!
55:
Not at all. It was a great opportunity
to learn about the future of our
kingdom.
62:
In these children, I see a future from
the curses of the past. We will walk
bravely forward, with naught but
good will and curiosity to guide us.
63:
That is surely a better path than the
rocky road the former king and I
were building.
68:
Hah, man, maybe I had you all
wrong.
73:
What are you doing! Do you know
who this man is?!
76:
Oh, we know alright! He's murdered
our comrades and taken our
villages countless times... It's that
damnable Black Wolf!
79:
Strike him down! Execute him on the
spot! Get revenge for my poor boy!
83:
Cut it out! Two wrongs don't make a
right!
87:
Rolf, you ain't got nothing to say for
yourself? At least claim your
innocence.
90:
No. I am proud of the work I did on
the battlefield. A warrior has no use
for shame.
91:
But... perhaps I may still find use as a
tribute.
93:
For those with their hearts and
minds stuck in the old ways, it's the
only way to ease their pain.
100: Stop it! He didn't do nothing wrong!
101:
Get over here this instant! Or he'll kill
you too!
103:
He wouldn't never do nothing like
that! Even if his fangs are scary!
107: I ask you... Could we settle this later?
110:
Oh, we sure will! This day has been a
long time coming!
118: Wait, our debt? That mob's debt?
121:
Sorry for the rough treatment. I
should've spoken up, but I...
123:
No, there's nothing to be said. I
behaved in a way that would bring
shame to my king. I'm sure you
would agree, Sir Nimbus.
130:
Hey, Claw. I think this old knight's
helmet is on too tight. What say we
get him some grub so he can relax?
135:
Now you're talking! You're going to
love my traditional feline fixings!
